00:40:38,803 --> 00:40:41,431
It doesn't make any difference.
It's in the hands of a jury.

654
00:40:41,505 --> 00:40:43,837
If they acquit, he walks.

655
00:40:43,908 --> 00:40:45,933
What, your jury's still out?
Five days.

656
00:40:46,010 --> 00:40:48,535
Well, they, like juries
all over the tristate area,

657
00:40:48,612 --> 00:40:52,013
will be rendering verdicts tonight
and tomorrow.

658
00:40:52,082 --> 00:40:55,245
You know this.
I know this.

659
00:40:55,319 --> 00:40:59,585
How?
Because play-offs start tomorrow.

660
00:41:03,394 --> 00:41:05,328
<i>Not guilty.</i>

661
00:41:06,464 --> 00:41:09,956
Guilty. Guilty.
Eleven to one.

662
00:41:13,270 --> 00:41:15,568
Please, you know in your heart
he killed her.

663
00:41:15,639 --> 00:41:20,576
I'm not even sure she's dead.
She could be in Japan or Brunei.

664
00:41:20,644 --> 00:41:24,910
She's dead, she's dead, she's dead,
and Kurt Lascher did it!

665
00:41:24,982 --> 00:41:27,576
Fine. Let's just
pick this up in the morning.

666
00:41:27,651 --> 00:41:31,246
<i>No, no, no. Let's stay here
until we get this settled.</i>

667
00:41:38,395 --> 00:41:41,387
Ladies and gentlemen of the jury,
have you reached a verdict?

668
00:41:41,465 --> 00:41:45,026
- We have, Your Honor.
- How say you?

669
00:41:47,471 --> 00:41:50,497
We find the defendant,
Kurt Lascher, guilty.

670
00:41:50,574 --> 00:41:53,566
[Murmuring]

671
00:42:03,187 --> 00:42:05,121
Thanks.

672
00:42:26,510 --> 00:42:29,377
Never saw it coming.
Thank God.

673
00:42:29,446 --> 00:42:32,313
That was a buzzer beater.
That was a three-point buzzer beater.

674
00:42:32,383 --> 00:42:36,717
You convicted a guy on cruelty to animals,
not evidence.

675
00:42:36,787 --> 00:42:38,778
Life's a bitch.
Yeah, and some days,

676
00:42:38,856 --> 00:42:41,882
the one holding the scales
is blind, deaf and dumb.

677
00:43:14,892 --> 00:43:17,326
<i>[Howling]</i>

